    <section id="about">
        <h1>About Barangay Roxas</h1>
        <div>
            <h2>History</h2>
            <p>
                Barangay Roxas is one of the most significant and well-known barangays in the city. Its historical
                development dates back to when it was established as a residential area surrounded by thriving business
                hubs.
            </p>
            <p>
                The barangay is named after Manuel A. Roxas, the fifth President of the Philippines and a notable leader
                in the country's political history. It has grown into a dynamic community that houses various
                institutions, public services, and cultural landmarks.
            </p>
            <p>
                Over the years, Barangay Roxas has remained steadfast in its commitment to fostering a safe, clean, and
                progressive environment for its residents. Its programs focus on improving public welfare, supporting
                education, and promoting local economic activities.
            </p>
        </div>
        <div>
            <h2>Mission</h2>
            <p>
                To provide inclusive and sustainable development, Barangay Roxas emphasizes community-based programs
                that focus on health, education, and livelihood opportunities for its residents.
            </p>
        </div>
        <div>
            <h2>Vision</h2>
            <p>
                A model barangay where every resident thrives in a safe, healthy, and well-organized community,
                upholding the values of unity, transparency, and progress.
            </p>
        </div>
    </section>


